\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli id=\"wprm-recipe-134135-step-0-1\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eShake for 10-15 seconds until well chilled.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli id=\"wprm-recipe-134135-step-0-2\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eStrain and pour into a martini glass (bonus points for using a chilled glass).\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli id=\"wprm-recipe-134135-step-0-3\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eGarnish with a lemon twist or a sprig of fresh rosemary.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e \n\n\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTo chill a martini glass, simply place it in the freezer for at least 30 minutes. This will make it nice and frosty. Remove it when you’re ready to serve your cocktail.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou can garnish the drink with fresh pomegranate seeds or even a wedge of pomegranate fruit if you like.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThis recipe makes the perfect holiday drink because pomegranate juice is more pigmented and makes a bright red color much more intense than cranberry juice (such as a Cosmopolitan) while tasting very similar. Garnishing with fresh rosemary sprigs adds to the holiday appeal.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIf you don’t have lemon juice, you can also use another citrus juice such as lime juice in its place.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTo make a pitcher recipe, increase this recipe for 6 servings. Serve in a pitcher with frozen cranberries to keep it chilled. Don’t add ice to the pitcher.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTry a sugar rim for a festive look.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\t\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\u003cdetails\u003e\n\n    \u003csummary\u003e\u003c/summary\u003e\n\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cp\u003eNutrition Facts\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003ePomegranate Martini\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAmount per Serving\